Mexican Stocks: America Movil, Grupo Modelo, Industrias Penoles

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-09-21T16:20:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-21/mexican-stocks-america-movil-grupo-modelo-industrias-penoles.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:57 a.m. New York time.  The IPC index rose 0.6 percent to 34,538.58.  Industrias Penoles SAB (PE&OLES* MM), Mexico’s largest
silver producer, gained 1 percent, its first advance in three
days, to 580 pesos as silver for December delivery rose 0.6
percent to $40.39 an ounce.  Retail sales in Mexico during July rose 3.1 percent, less
than the 3.9 percent average of a Bloomberg survey of 12
economists. “While retail sales disappointed and was below
consensus, they continued a healthy expansion,” Nomura Holdings
strategist  Benito Berber  wrote in a note to clients today.
“There is still a lot of room for credit to grow, which
eventually will support domestic consumption.”  Grupo Modelo SA (GMODELOC MM), Mexico’s largest beer maker,
advanced 3.1 percent to 80.20 pesos.  America Movil  SAB (AMXL MM), the largest wireless carrier
in the Americas by subscribers, rose 1.3 percent to 15.73 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Leon Lazaroff in New York at 
 llazaroff@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
